iterator iter[K, V](self: PyDict[K, V]): K
Warning: Nim's for stmt calls items implicitly, instead of iter so beware to always write iter for dict in for loop

Example:

let d = dict(a=1)
for i in iter(d):
  assert i == "a"
for i in d:
  assert i[0] == "a" and i[1] == 1
